{
  "openapi": "3.0.3",
  "info": {
    "version": "2017-09-01",
    "title": "platform-api-admin-token",
    "description": "A loosely [OAuth 2.0](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749) compliant authentication service used to obtain bearer tokens for use with the CloudLink Platform micro-service APIs.\n\n# Endpoints\n- /token is for [OAuth 2.0](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749) grants.\n- /assume-role/token can be used to switch account or role (subject to permissions) for a logged in user or client.\n- /guest/token can be used to obtain an anonymous user access token with limited access rights (guest level access).\n- /authorize can be used by a registered client application to initiate an [Authorization Code Grant](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749#section-4.1) authorization flow.\n- /policy-test can be used to test a set of resources against a user's access policy.\n- /applications can be used to manage the application registry.\n- /credentials is an internal API that can be used to perform actions on stored credentials.\n- /.well-known/jwks is the JSON Web Key Set endpoint for an account.\n- /trusted-issuers is used to configure the trusted token issuers for an account.\n# Supported OAuth 2.0 grants\n- password - [Resource Owner Password Credentials Flow](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749#section-4.3)\n- client_credentials - [Client Credentials Flow](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749#section-4.4)\n- refresh_token - [Refreshing an Access Token](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749#page-47)\n- authorization_code - [Authorization Code Grant](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749#section-4.1)\n- urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:token-exchange - [OAuth 2.0 Token Exchange](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc8693) - For Zoom clients\n\nInput arguments may be passed either as `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` pairs in the request body and/or in a basic auth header.\n# OAuth 2.0 Grants\nOAuth 2.0 requests are handled by the `/token` endpoint.\n## Login using username and password\nDuring user login, the platform checks that the user and account are active and that the password is valid.\n\nThe username identifies the user, it is matched against the user's `userId`, `uniqueUserId`, `email`, `mobile` or `loginId` properties.\n\nExample:\n\n`grant_type=password&username=jsmith%40somecompany.com&password=****`\n\nIf the request is successful the response is `201 (Created)` and access/refresh tokens are returned.  If the username or password are incorrect then the response is `401 (Unauthorized)`.\n## Login using username, password and account ID\nIf the `/token` endpoint returns 409 (Conflict) the username may be present in more than one account.  Provide the account ID to select which account to log the user into:\n\n`grant_type=password&username=jsmith%40somecompany.com&password=****&account_id=4321`\n\nIf the request is successful the response is `201 (Created)` and access/refresh tokens are returned.  If the username or password are incorrect then the response is `401 (Unauthorized)`.\n## Refresh token to obtain fresh tokens\nAccess tokens are valid for (by default) 1 hour, the platform also returns a fresh token which is valid for (by default) 14 days and can be used to obtain fresh access and refresh tokens.  During refresh, the platform checks that the account and user are still active.\n\n`grant_type=refresh_token&refresh_token=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx`\n\nIf the request is successful the response is `201 (Created)` and access/refresh tokens are returned.  If the token is not valid then the response is `401 (Unauthorized)`.  If the user or account is not active then the response is `403 (Forbidden)`.\n## Client login using client ID and secret\nDuring client login, the platform checks that the client and account are active and that the client secret is valid.\n\n`grant_type=client_credentials&client_id=9552c9497d624b75a7399fdb494abb1e&client_secret=******`\n\nIf the request is successful the response is `201 (Created)` and access/refresh tokens are returned.  If the client ID or secret are incorrect then the response is `401 (Unauthorized)`.\n## Client login with basic auth header\nClients in possession of a client password MAY use the HTTP Basic authentication scheme as defined in [RFC2617](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749#section-2.3.1) to authenticate with the authorization server.  The client identifier is encoded using the `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` encoding algorithm, and the encoded value is used as the username; the client password is encoded using the same algorithm and used as the password.\n\nheader:\n\n`Authorization: 'Basic bXfecHB1UTIyNA=='`\n\nbody:\n\n`grant_type=client_credentials`\n\nIf the encoded username and password are valid and the request is successful then the response is `201 (Created)` and access/refresh tokens are returned.  If the username or password are invalid then the response is `401 (Unauthorized)`.\n\n# Authorization Code Grant Flow\nAuthorization is initiated using the `/authorize` endpooint.  In order to use this route, the application must be registered in the platform and a client ID created for the application.  Also any redirect URL(s) which are valid for the application need to be pre-registered.\n\nThe application wishing to log in a user and obtain a user token begins by redirecting the user agent (browser) to an authentication portal such as the Mitel global auth portal, providing client ID, response type, redirect URI, state and application name:\n\n```\n  HTTP 1.1 302 Found\n  https://auth.mitel.io/authorize?\n  client_id=bca4584614724174b8290bdd6c7d5967\n  &response_type=code\n  &redirect_uri=https://some.app.mitel.io\n  &state=abc\n  &app_name=SomeApp\n```\n\nThe authentication portal will ask the user for thier username, password and possibly thier account ID if the username is present in multiple accounts.  It will then initiate Oauth authorization by sending a POST request to the /authorize endpoint with the following parameters:\n\n- client_id is the pre-registered client ID for the application.\n- response_type: code is the only currently supported response type.\n- username will be used to identify the user.\n- password is the user's password.\n- account_id can be provided if the platform returns 409 (Conflict) because the username exists in more that one account.\n- redirect_uri is the URI to re-direct the user agent to, after successful login.\n\nThe platform then logs the user in by generating access and refresh tokens, they are stored ready to be retrieved by the application and an authorization code is returned to the auth portal, to pass along to the calling application.\n\nDuring user login, the platform checks that the user and account are active and that the password is valid.\n\nThe username identifies the user, it is matched against the user's `userId`, `uniqueUserId`, `email`, `mobile` or `loginId` properties.\n\nExample (posted to /authorize):\n\n`client_id=bc81084614724174b8290bdd6c7d5967&response_type=code&username=jsmith%40somecompany.com&password=****&account_id=1234&redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Faccounts.dev.mitel.io`\n\nThe application will then send the auth code to the `/token` endpoint using the authorization_code flow.\n\nExample (posted to /token):\n\n`grant_type=authorization_code&client_id=bc81084614724174b8290bdd6c7d5967&code=d09fea34-d053-4b80-9bdc-f7d0ffd3b2bd&scope=abc`\n\nNote that auth codes are only stored in the auth service for a period of time.   If the application waits too long, the auth code may have expired.\n\nIf the request is successful the response is `201 (Created)` and access/refresh tokens are returned.  If the code is not valid or has expired then the response is `401 (Unauthorized)`.  If the user or account is not active then the response is `403 (Forbidden)`.\n# Assume Role Feature\nIt is often useful for a partner administrator to switch accounts, to one of the accounts that they administer, as an account administrator, or for an account administrator to assume a user role to limit the effect of unintended requests.  The platform provides an authenticated route for this purpose, served by the `/assume-role/token` endpoint.\n\nA logged in administrator can use this route to issue a token in a different account or with a lower role (depending on thier permissions).\n\nA logged in client can use this route to issue an anonymous user token in a different account or with a lower role (depending on thier permissions).\n\n## Administrator assuming a user role in a different account\nExample:\n\n```\n{\n    \"accountId\": \"1234\",\n  \"role\": \"USER\"\n}\n```\n\n## Guest Access\nGuest access allows an unauthenticated client to obtain access to an account with extremely limited usage rights.  Guest access must be explicitly enabled by turning on an account policy.  The client simply provides a guest principal ID (which can be anything, a generated UUID would be a good choice) and the name of the user to the `/guest/token` route.\n\nExample:\n\n```\n{\n    \"principalId\": \"7688c81e-c6ea-4777-a1a2-8163ed318a19\",\n  \"accountId\": \"1234\",\n  \"name\": \"Guest User One\"\n}\n```\n\nIf the request is successful the response is `201 (Created)` and access/refresh tokens are returned.  If the account is not active, if the principal ID identifies a legitimate platform user or the account is not enabled with the guest access policy then the response is `403 (Forbidden)` (user impersonation is not allowed by any route).",
    "termsOfService": "https://mitel.io/terms-of-service",
    "contact": {
      "name": "CloudLink support",
      "email": "cloudlink.support@mitel.io",
      "url": "https://mitel.io/support"
    },
    "license": {
      "name": "Mitel",
      "url": "https://www.mitel.com/legal"
    },
    "x-jentic-source-url": "https://authentication.api.mitel.io/2017-09-01/_spec"
  },
  "servers": [
    {
      "url": "https://authentication.api.mitel.io/2017-09-01"
    }
  ],
  "components": {
    "schemas": {
      "token": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": [
          "token_type",
          "expires_in",
          "access_token",
          "refresh_token",
          "scope"
        ],
        "properties": {
          "token_type": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The type of the token, typically bearer"
          },
          "expires_in": {
            "type": "number",
            "description": "The lifetime in seconds of the access_token"
          },
          "access_token": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The access token used to authenticate against secure resources"
          },
          "refresh_token": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "A token used to obtain a new access token without re-authenticating"
          },
          "scope": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The scope of the access_token"
          },
          "gauth": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "sso": {
            "type": "object",
            "description": "Additional sso tokens for social media sign-on",
            "properties": {
              "provider": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "The name of the social media provider"
              },
              "accessToken": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "The access token used to authenticate against the given provider"
              },
              "refreshToken": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "The refresh token used to authenticate against the given provider"
              }
            }
          },
          "issued_token_type": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "For token-exchange flow this indicates the returned token type"
          }
        }
      },
      "claims": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": [
          "principalId",
          "accountId",
          "role",
          "exp"
        ],
        "properties": {
          "principalId": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "accountId": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "role": {
            "type": "string",
            "enum": [
              "GLOBAL_ADMIN",
              "PARTNER_ADMIN",
              "ACCOUNT_ADMIN",
              "USER",
              "GUEST"
            ]
          },
          "exp": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      },
      "oauthClientConfig": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": [
          "clientId"
        ],
        "properties": {
          "clientId": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "pkce": {
            "type": "string",
            "enum": [
              "plain",
              "S256"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "resource": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "createdOn": {
            "type": "string",
            "format": "date-time"
          },
          "createdBy": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "modifiedOn": {
            "type": "string",
            "format": "date-time"
          },
          "modifiedBy": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "_links": {
            "type": "object",
            "description": "hypermedia links",
            "required": [
              "self"
            ],
            "properties": {
              "self": {
                "type": "string"
              }
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "resourceCollection": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": [
          "_links"
        ],
        "properties": {
          "_links": {
            "type": "object",
            "description": "hypermedia links",
            "required": [
              "self"
            ],
            "properties": {
              "self": {
                "type": "string"
              }
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "assumeRoleTokenPostRequest": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": [
          "role"
        ],
        "properties": {
          "accountId": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Assume role to this account."
          },
          "role": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Role to be assumed."
          },
          "policyId": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The policy to be assumed (used in assume-policy flow)."
          }
        }
      },
      "authCode": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": [
          "code"
        ],
        "properties": {
          "code": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Authorization code"
          }
        }
      },
      "ConflictResponse": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": [
          "message",
          "name"
        ],
        "properties": {
          "message": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "name": {
            "type": "string",
            "enum": [
              "ConditionalCheckFailedException",
              "MultipleMatching"
            ]
          },
          "labels": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "SamlResponse": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "code": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Authorization code"
          },
          "state": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Application State"
          },
          "error": {
            "type": "string",
            "enum": [
              "invalid_request",
              "access_denied"
            ]
          },
          "error_description": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        }
      },
      "UnauthorizedBaseResponse": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "message": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Unauthorized"
          },
          "name": {
            "type": "string",
            "enum": [
              "MissingContext"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "ForbiddenBaseResponse": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "message": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Insufficient Permissions"
          },
          "name": {
            "type": "string",
            "enum": [
              "InsufficientPermissions"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "policyTestCriteria": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": [
          "resource"
        ],
        "description": "Test criteria which describes the access desired (an action, applied to a resource)",
        "properties": {
          "resource": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "a resource to access"
          },
          "action": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "an action to perform on the resource. default * = any"
          },
          "accountId": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "an alternate account ID to run policy against."
          },
          "context": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "additional context to use in evaluating policies with conditions."
          }
        }
      },
      "policyTestRequest": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": [
          "resources"
        ],
        "properties": {
          "resources": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/policyTestCriteria"
            }
          },
          "principalId": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "an alternate identity of a user in our system to run policy against"
          },
          "types": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
              "type": "string"
            },
            "description": "A list of policy types on the account that will be included in the policy test. Currently only a single additional type is supported. If omitted the default system, account, and principal policies will be tested."
          }
        }
      },
      "policyTestResult": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": [
          "resource",
          "effect",
          "policyName",
          "version"
        ],
        "description": "The effect granted by a  policy statement, whether specified action is allowed on the specified resource",
        "properties": {
          "resource": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "a resource to access"
          },
          "action": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "an action to perform on the resource. default * = any"
          },
          "effect": {
            "type": "string",
            "enum": [
              "ExplicitAllow",
              "ExplicitDeny",
              "ImplicitAllow",
              "ImplicitDeny"
            ],
            "description": "policy statement effect"
          },
          "statementId": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "the statement that caused the effect"
          },
          "policyName": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "the policy document name that contained the statement"
          },
          "version": {
            "type": "number",
            "description": "the policy document version that contained the statement"
          },
          "accountId": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "the alternate account ID that the policy was run against"
          },
          "limit": {
            "type": "number",
            "description": "An optional field indicating the limit associated with this resource. The limit is only returned when making a request with action \"limit\" and if it is present on the statement that set the returned effect."
          }
        }
      },
      "policyTestResponse": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "principalId": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "the principalId for which the policy was evaluated for"
          },
          "results": {
            "type": "array",
            "description": "an array of results based on the input statements to evaluate",
            "items": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/policyTestResult"
            }
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "principalId",
          "results"
        ]
      },
      "ssoProvider": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "providerId": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The named provider used to authenticate"
          },
          "signonUrl": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The url used during login in to create an <a href... link to trigger the authentication flow"
          },
          "scopes": {
            "type": "array",
            "description": "The default scopes that will be requested in the authentication flow",
            "items": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          "name": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The label name for the provider button"
          },
          "signupUrl": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The url used during signup to create an <a href... link to trigger the authentication flow"
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "providerId",
          "signonUrl",
          "scopes"
        ]
      },
      "ssoProviderResults": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "providers": {
            "type": "array",
            "description": "An array of sso providers based on the requesting profile",
            "items": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ssoProvider"
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "ssoProviderRequest": {
        "allOf": [
          {
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ssoProvider"
          },
          {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "clientId": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "The 3rd party client application ID for the SSO provider"
              },
              "clientSecret": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "The 3rd party client application secret for the SSO provider"
              },
              "callbackUrl": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "The url used during signon for the sso provider to call back into"
              }
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      "legacyApplication": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "name": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The name of the application"
          },
          "active": {
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "Application is active or not"
          },
          "logoUrl": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The Application Logo URL"
          },
          "providers": {
            "type": "array",
            "description": "An array of sso providers based on the requesting profile",
            "items": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ssoProvider"
            }
          },
          "theme": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Theme used to render the Auth Portal"
          },
          "links": {
            "type": "array",
            "description": "An array of links associated with this application. For example, Support or Legal links",
            "items": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/appLink"
            }
          },
          "passwordRules": {
            "type": "array",
            "description": "Set of password rules for this application",
            "items": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/passwordRule"
            }
          },
          "requiredAttributes": {
            "type": "array",
            "description": "An array of user attributes required for the users of this application other than name or email.",
            "items": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          "optionalAttributes": {
            "type": "array",
            "description": "An array of user attributes that are optional for the users of this application other than name or email.",
            "items": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          "supportedCountries": {
            "type": "array",
            "description": "An array of supported countries in ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 format for this application",
            "items": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          "requestCountry": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The cloudfront viewer country of the requestor if available"
          }
        }
      },
      "application": {
        "allOf": [
          {
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/resource"
          },
          {
            "type": "object",
            "required": [
              "applicationId",
              "accountId",
              "partnerId",
              "active"
            ],
            "properties": {
              "applicationId": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "The client application identifier"
              },
              "accountId": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "The account ID of this application data"
              },
              "partnerId": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "The partner ID of this application data"
              },
              "name": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "The name of the application"
              },
              "description": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "The description of this application"
              },
              "active": {
                "type": "boolean",
                "description": "Application is active or not"
              },
              "redirectUris": {
                "type": "array",
                "description": "An array of URIs for the given application",
                "items": {
                  "type": "string"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      "applicationCollection": {
        "allOf": [
          {
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/resourceCollection"
          },
          {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "_embedded": {
                "type": "object",
                "required": [
                  "items"
                ],
                "description": "Used for embedded objects",
                "properties": {
                  "items": {
                    "type": "array",
                    "items": {
                      "$ref": "#/components/schemas/application"
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      "appLink": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "name": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The name of the link"
          },
          "url": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The url of the link"
          },
          "version": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The version of the link needed for certain applications to reference a version of a particular url."
          },
          "disableAutoNavigate": {
            "type": "boolean",
            "default": false,
            "description": "Indicates if the auto-forwarding capability of the portal should be disabled."
          }
        }
      },
      "passwordRule": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "minLength": {
            "type": "number",
            "description": "Minimum length of password"
          },
          "maxLength": {
            "type": "number",
            "description": "Maximum length of password"
          },
          "mustContain": {
            "type": "array",
            "description": "The password must contain at least one of these characters",
            "items": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          "mustContainNumber": {
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "Whether the password must contain a number or not"
          },
          "mustContainLetter": {
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "Whether the password must contain a letter or not"
          },
          "mustContainUpperAndLowercaseLetters": {
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "The password must contain at least one lower and one upper case letter"
          },
          "mustNotContainSpaces": {
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "Whether the password must not contain a space or not"
          }
        }
      },
      "statusGetResponse": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "status": {
            "type": "string",
            "enum": [
              "Red",
              "Yellow",
              "Green"
            ],
            "description": "Overall status of the microservice."
          },
          "errorRate": {
            "type": "object",
            "description": "Provides the error count for the microservice in a given time period",
            "properties": {
              "last15Minutes": {
                "type": "number",
                "description": "Provides the error count for the microservice in the last 15 minutes"
              }
            }
          },
          "responseTime": {
            "type": "object",
            "description": "Provides the average response time for the microservice in a given time period",
            "properties": {
              "last15Minutes": {
                "type": "number",
                "description": "Provides the error count for the microservice in the last 15 minutes"
              }
            }
          },
          "messages": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
              "type": "string"
            },
            "description": "Array of messages to be returned providing more detail on the status of the service."
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "status",
          "errorRate",
          "responseTime",
          "messages"
        ],
        "additionalProperties": false
      },
